location_string: Khao Thong, Krabi Town, Krabi Province
description: Bac-a-Sable is difficult to find but definitively worth the pain. It is located at the north end of Thalane beach but easier to access through the hotel Le Passe-Temps, which entrance way starts on the right hand side when going towards the pier to Koh Yao Noi & Yai, some 3 kilometers after the Khao Thong Terrace. The menu is part Thai (chicken cashew nuts, fried rice, phat thai, curries...) Part international (bbq, plancha, mixed salads, home made hamburgers, club sandwich, french fries...). The staff doesn't know much of english but the menu is tranlated in French and English and the French manager is usually around to help. The food is perfectly alright, still what truly make the difference here, - apart from the cool beer which is not that easy to find in this muslim area - is the view. You'll have lunch your feet in the sand, in the shade of the trees, just meters from the sea and its amazing rocks. No one around except the passing fishermen and the few villagers looking for shells and crabs at low tide. You'll find more than easy to spend the rest of you day in a hammock, waiting for the sunset !
